Pre-Game Insights: The Suns have won the first two matchups of the season against the Jazz.
The Suns have won eight-straight games over the Jazz, their second-longest winning streak over Utah in series history.
The Suns swept Utah last season, the first time doing so since a 3-0 record against Utah during the 2020-21 season.
The Suns have won 15 of the last 17 meetings and lead the all-time series 107-95.
Others: The Suns improved to 17-19 on the season following a 123-115 win over the Hawks on Jan. 10.
Bradley Beal posted a game-high 25 points on 11-of-16 shooting and 7 rebounds in the game against the Hawks.
Kevin Durant finished with 23 points on 9-of-15 shooting from the field and 7 assists in the game against the Hawks.
Devin Booker tallied 20 points and matched his season high for assists with a game-high 12 in the game against the Hawks.
Grayson Allen had a season-high 23 points on 7-of-8 shooting in 27 minutes off the bench in the game against the Hawks.
